text: Land's End is a headland in western Cornwall, England. It is the westernmost point of mainland Cornwall and England. Land's End is at the end of the Penwith peninsula. It is about west-south-west of Penzance at the western end of the A30 main road.Ordnance Survey: Landranger map sheet 203 Land's End A modern holiday complex has been built nearby. Land's End is from John o' Groats in Scotland by road. == References == Category:Geography of Cornwall Category:Capes
